NYE 2025 TfNSW Interactive Road Closure and Clearway map

properties.publicTransport: Buses are diverting due to closures. Buses that usually run to Blue St North Sydney station will use stops on Berry St and Miller St near McLaren St. McMahons Point wharf and Milsons Point wharf are both closed. Use trains or buses and walk instead. Trains from the city will not stop at Milsons Pt from 6pm. Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
With major road closures and parking restrictions in place this New Year's Eve attendees should leave the car at home and catch public transport instead.

Roads have started closing ahead of major closures in North Sydney CBD close from 3pm and from 5pm in Milsons Point, Kirribilli and Lavender Bay. Roads will reopen by 3am on 1 January.

Key road closure timings:

  • *CLOSED* 7pm 30 Dec – 3am 1 Jan: harbourfront roads around vantage points in Milsons Point, Kirribilli and McMahons Point are closed including Blues Point Rd, Lavender Cres, Kirribilli Ave, Olympic Dr, Broughton St, Pitt St, Railway Ave and Henry Lawson Ave.
  • *CLOSED* The Cahill Expressway and all on and off ramps remain closed until 6am NYD.
  • *CLOSED* 8am 31 Dec – 3am 1 Jan: sections of Blues Point Rd from French St, Alfred St Sth and local roads surrounding vantage points. 
  • *CLOSED* 12pm 31 Dec - 3am 1 Jan: Fitzroy St between Alfred St South and Broughton St. Use High St instead.
  • *CLOSED* 3pm 31 Dec – 3am 1 Jan: Blue St at North Sydney Station and Ennis Rd from Broughton St at Milsons Point Station is closed.
  • *CLOSED* 5pm 31 Dec – 3am 1 Jan: more major roads are closed in North Sydney, McMahons Point, Milsons Point and Waverton including sections of Miller St, Blues Point Rd, Lavender St, Union St, Balls Head Rd, Pacific Hwy southbound, Alfred St South, Walker St, Denison St and surrounding local roads. 
  • From 5pm access to Kirribilli and Milsons Point is via Military Rd only due to the closure of Pacific Hwy southbound.
  • *CLOSED* 8pm 31 Dec – 3am 1 Jan: the Pacific Hwy northbound off ramp to North Sydney from Sydney Harbour Bridge is closed. Use the Miller St or Military Rd off-ramps instead for access to North Sydney.
  • 11pm – 1.30am: Sydney Harbour Bridge closed in both directions and Western Distributor fully closed between Pyrmont and the city. Arthur St southbound between Berry St and Mount St, all traffic to turn left on to Warringah Fwy northbound.

Special event clearways are in effect on various roads in Kirribilli, Lavender Bay, McMahons Point, Milsons Point and North Sydney between 1pm NYE and 3am NYD.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones for all vehicle types, and apply even to local residents and TfNSW Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in signposted clearways will be towed and a fee applies. If your vehicle is towed, you can search your vehicle registration at the Find My Car website to find its new location, or alternatively call 132 701 to speak to an operator.

Road closures and restricted access arrangements are in place as crowds gather to celebrate New Year's Eve in Kurraba Point.

From 5pm NYE to 3am 1 Jan the following roads into Kurraba Point are closed. Access will be maintained by traffic control for residents only until 8pm. After 8pm no vehicle access permitted.

  • Kurraba Rd from Wycombe Rd,
  • Wallaringa Ave from Lower Wycombe Rd
  • Shellcove Rd from Harriette St

Special event clearways are in effect on nearby major roads including Falcon St and Military Rd between Crows Nest and Mosman from 3pm to 3am.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones for all vehicle types, and apply even to local residents and TfNSW Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in signposted clearways will be towed and a fee applies. If your vehicle is towed, you can search your vehicle registration at the Find My Car website to find its new location, or alternatively call 132 701 to speak to an operator.

properties.otherAdvice:
Road closures and clearways are in place for New Year's Eve (NYE) at Taronga Zoo in Mosman. Parking is very limited in the area and Zoo parking will fill quickly, consider the public transport options.

  • **CLOSED from 3pm NYE until 2am New Year's Day (NYD): Bradleys Head Rd and Athol Wharf Rd approaching the Zoo
  • **CLOSED from 11.30pm NYE until 2am NYD: sections of Bradley's Head Rd, Prince Albert St, Thompson St and Whiting Beach Rd are closed.

Special event clearways are in effect at the following times and locations:

  • From 1pm NYE to 3am NYD on sections of Spit Rd, Athol Wharf Rd, Bradley Head Rd and Whiting Beach Rd.
  • Clearways are also in effect along Falcon St and Military Rd between Spit Rd, Mosman and the Pacific Hwy, Crows Nest on both sides since 3pm NYE until 3am NYD
  • From 6pm NYE to 3am NYD on sections of Military Rd near Belmont Rd and Mandolong Rd.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones for all vehicle types, and apply even to local residents and TfNSW Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in signposted clearways will be towed and a fee applies. If your vehicle is towed, you can search your vehicle registration at the Find My Car website to find its new location, or alternatively call 132 701 to speak to an operator.

properties.publicTransport: Transport services have returned to normal routes as road closures have lifted. Visit transportnsw.info/sydney-nye for details.
properties.otherAdvice:
Most major roads have reopened in the Sydney CBD following the 2025 NYE fireworks displays.

Some roads are still closed until 6am for event pack down.

KEY ROADS REMAIN CLOSED:

  • The Cahill Expressway southbound lanes 7 and 8 on the Harbour Bridge and Circular Quay Overpass closed until 6am NYD. 
  • A section of Macquarie St north of Bridge St remains closed until 6am.

properties.publicTransport: Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
Illawarra Hotel NYE Block will take place on 31 December, road closures will be in place from 6am Wednesday until 6am Thursday.

Traffic controllers will be on site to direct motorists.

Motorists should detour via adjacent streets and be aware of increased pedestrian activity on local roads
The TFW 9s competition will be held 8-10 Jan, 12-14 Jan & 16-18 Jan. Motorists are advised to follow signage, traffic control and be aware of increased pedestrian activity during the event.

properties.publicTransport: Route 15 Helensburgh to Stanwell Park bus services will run to a Sunday timetable on Christmas Day. Services will run every 30 minutes on New Years Day starting from Helensburgh Station at 8:57am.
properties.otherAdvice: Heavy traffic may be experienced on Lawrence Hargrave Dr during Christmas Day and New Years Day celebrations with large numbers of visitors expected at the temple.
properties.displayName: Sri Venkateswara Temple Christmas and New Year celebrations

properties.publicTransport: Match tickets include travel on transport. Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
A-League Men: Western Sydney Wanderers v Macarthur FC at CommBank Stadium. Kick-off at 7pm, finish around 8.55pm.

Traffic will be heavier than usual on roads approaching the stadium as fans travel to the match. Allow extra travel time on roads including Parramatta Road, Church Street, Victoria Road, James Ruse Drive and Pennant Hills Road. 

Motorists should also exercise caution as pedestrian activity will be high on roads between Parramatta Interchange and the stadium. 

Be patient leaving car parks as traffic will be heavy and follow the directions of traffic controllers and Police.

properties.publicTransport: Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
Field Day music festival at The Domain Sydney on New Year's Day from 12pm to 11pm.

With thousands of people expected, traffic will be heavier than usual within the Sydney CBD on Macquarie St, College St and William St.

Roads around The Domain Sydney will close for crowd safety before, during and after the event.

Motorists should avoid driving through the area or expect delays and detours, and watch out for pedestrians in the area.

Road closures

From 7pm until midnight approx.: Art Gallery Road will be closed to incoming traffic.

From 10pm until midnight approx.:

  • Art Gallery Road from Hospital Road to Mrs Macquarie Road
  • St Marys Rd from Prince Albert Road to Sir John Young Crescent
  • Prince Albert Road from Macquarie Street to Art Gallery Road
  • Hospital Road from Art Gallery Road to Shakespeare Place
  • Macquarie Street from Hunter Street to Prince Albert Road
  • St James Road from Elizabeth Street to Macquarie Street
  • College Street from Park Street to Prince Albert Road
  • Cathedral Street at St Marys Road

If you are catching rideshare or taxis, use the dedicated drop-off location on Hospital Road at Art Gallery Road. For pick-ups after the event head towards Elizabeth Street or Sir John Young Crescent.
